Technology,
 Incentives,
 and the Emergence of Markets for Quality:
 Evidence from Ugandan Dairy Supply Chains
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Quality in agri-food supply chains is often unobservable at first sale,
 and early aggregation limits traceability,
 weakening incentives for quality provision.
 We study whether improving measurement and traceability induces quality-based incentives in Uganda’s dairy sector.
 In a cluster randomized trial with 130 milk collection centers and 2,600 farmers,
 we introduce digital milk analyzers and record-keeping systems.
 The intervention improves milk quality,
 primarily by reducing adulteration,
 but does not raise prices.
 Randomized quality premiums further improve quality when binding,
 yet are not passed through to farmers,
 highlighting frictions in vertical transmission within smallholder value chains.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In many agri-food supply chains,
 quality is difficult to verify at the point of first sale,
 and early aggregation of output from multiple suppliers limits traceability,
 weakening the link between producer effort and returns.
 We study whether improving the visibility and traceability of raw milk quality induces quality-based incentives in Uganda’s dairy sector.
 Working with 130 milk collection centers and 2,600 farmers,
 we implement a cluster randomized controlled trial that introduces digital milk analyzers and record-keeping systems.
 The intervention improves milk quality,
 primarily by reducing adulteration,
 but does not raise prices.
 In a second stage,
 we collaborate with collection centers to introduce randomized quality premiums targeting upstream suppliers.
 When binding,
 these premiums further improve quality,
 yet are not passed through to farmers.
 Together,
 these results highlight that while improved measurement can change behavior,
 it is not sufficient to generate effective price incentives,
 pointing to frictions in vertical transmission within smallholder value chains.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

